            <section id="sec1">
                <p><b>INTRODUCTION OF WAVES</b></p>
                <article>
                    A wave is a disturbance which travels outward from its source, carrying energy along with it. For
                    example, sets up a circular ring of disturbance(up and down motion of water particles) which travels
                    outward from the point at which the stone landed in the water (fig 1.1). This disturbance is called
                    <b>water wave.</b>
                    <figure><img src="wave.jpg" height="150" width="250" alt="image  not found">FIG 1.1</figure>
                </article>
            </section>
            <section id="sec2">
                <p><b>TYPES OF WAVES</b></p>
                <article>
                    They can be classified into two:<br>
                    <b>Material medium;</b><br>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Mechanical wave e.gwater wave,sound wave</li>
                        <li>Electromagnetic wavee.light wave,ultra-violet,radio wavee.t.c</li>
                    </ul><br><br>
                    <b>Direction of propagation;</b><br>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Transverse wave(perpendicular) e.gwater wave,light,radio waves etc.</li>
                        <li>Longitudinal wave(parallel) e.gsound wave</li>
                    </ul>
                </article>
            </section>
            <section id="sec3">
                <p><b>TERMS USED IN WAVE</b></p>
                <article>
                    <ol type="I">
                        <li>Crest</li>
                        <li>Trough</li>
                        <li>Amplitude</li>
                        <li>Wavelength</li>
                        <li>frequency</li>
                        <li>Period</li>
                        <li>velocity e.t.c</li>
                    </ol>
                </article>
                <figure><img src="terminologies.jpg" height="200" width="300">FIG 1.2</figure>
            </section>
            <section id="sec4">
                <p><b>PROPERTIES OF WAVE</b></p>
                <article>
                    <ol type="I">
                        <li>Reflection</li>
                        <li>Refraction</li>
                        <li>Diffraction</li>
                        <li>Polarisation</li>
                        <li>Interference</li>
                    </ol>
                </article>
